column4: any ideas why open office wont start after doing an update the other day?
1185 people in here and i'm the ONLY one that updated a system and open office wont work at all?
y not trying to reinstall openoffice.org using synaptic?
then do the purge command i gave b4 then do sudo apt-get install openoffice.org again see if that works
if ur in a rush and need an office suit right away u can temporarily use abiword for typed stuff and gnumeric for excel stuff

i dont think so, if its new, reboot ur live cd check it for errors then use it in live cd mode to see if openoffice.org works and if it does then reinstall and since its a new install u wont have anything to lose
im sry but think of it in the positive way, ur comp will still be usable wile ur reinstalling
